# npm access token — manual publish backup only.
#
# Primary path: CI publishes via OIDC Trusted Publishing (no token needed).
# This token is only for human-driven manual publishes when CI is unavailable.
# It is NEVER used in CI.
#
# Generate at: https://www.npmjs.com/settings/<your-username>/tokens
#   Type: Granular Access Token
#   Scope: read+write for @acme-skunkworks/npm-package-template (or the org)
#   Expiry: 30–90 days recommended
#   CRITICAL: tick "Bypass 2FA" / "Allow this token to bypass 2FA" at creation.
#   Tokens are immutable — if you forget the flag, you must revoke and regenerate.
#   Without bypass-2FA, every publish hits EOTP and you cannot proceed.
#
# Note: bypass-2FA tokens DO NOT work for the very first publish of a brand-new
# package. npm enforces 2FA on package creation regardless of token settings.
# See CLAUDE.md "Bootstrap publish" for the recovery-code workaround.
#
# To use this token (after the package exists on npm):
#   1. Copy this file to .env and fill in the token below.
#   2. Wire it into ~/.npmrc:
#        NPM_TOKEN=$(grep '^NPM_TOKEN=' .env | cut -d'=' -f2-)
#        npm config set //registry.npmjs.org/:_authToken "$NPM_TOKEN"
#        npm whoami    # verify
#   3. Then `pnpm run release:manual` (or `release:manual:dry` to simulate).
#
# Putting NPM_TOKEN in .env alone does not authenticate npm publish — the npm
# CLI does not read .env files. Step 2 is required.
#
# Never commit .env. It's already in .gitignore.
NPM_TOKEN=
